8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 209, L.D. 309, “An Act to Allow a
10 Political Party to Determine How That Party's Nominee Is Selected in a Primary Election”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 3 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 3. 21-A MRSA §321, sub-§2, ¶G is enacted to read:
13 G. Determine if the party's primary election to be held for the general election
14 following the next general election after the party's convention will be determined by
15 a plurality of votes cast in that election or by applying a ranked-choice voting count
16 pursuant to section 723-A. The party's determination must be incorporated into party
17 rules.'
18 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 4.
19 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 5 and inserting the following:
20 'Sec. 5. 21-A MRSA §723-A, sub-§5-D is enacted to read:
21 5-D. Opt-out for party primaries. A political party may opt out from the provisions
22 of this section for the party's primary election and cause the primary election to be
23 determined by a plurality of votes cast in that primary election if the party's convention
24 under section 321 votes to opt out of applying a ranked-choice voting count for the party's
25 primary election to be held for the general election following the next general election after
26 the party's convention and that determination is incorporated into the party's rules.'
27 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
28 number to read consecutively.
29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment provides that a political party during the party's state convention held
3311 between March 1st and August 1st biennially during each general election year must
3322 determine whether the party's primary election to be held for the general election following
3333 the next general election after the convention will be determined by ranked-choice voting
